    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se7/html/jls-10.html#jls-10.3\">JLS</a> clearly says</p>\n\n<p><strong>An array initializer creates an array and provides initial values for all its components.</strong> </p>\n\n<p>and this is irrespective of whether the array is an instance variable or local variable or class variable.</p>\n\n<p>Default values for primitive types : <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/datatypes.html\">docs</a></p>\n\n<p>For objects default values is <code>null</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
